title: Key Moments From the Pro-Palestinian Marches Across the U.S.
description: Thousands of pro-Palestinian protesters took to streets across the U.S. on Nov. 4, calling for a Gaza ceasefire amid the Israel-Hamas war.

title: Tamirat Tola Sets NYC Marathon Course Record to Win Men’s Race
description: Tamirat Tola broke the 12-year-old mark, finishing the race in 2 hours, 4 minutes and 58 seconds. Hellen Obiri won the women's race.

title: Japanese Rockstar Yoshiki Opens Up
description: Legendary Japanese rockstar Yoshiki Hayashi has had a death wish since he was 10. He also plans to become immortal.

title: People With Disabilities in Gaza Face Additional Barriers in the Israel-Hamas War
description: People with disabilities in Gaza are suffering disproportionate harm in the Israel-Hamas war, international aid organizations warn.

title: Warplanes Strike Gaza Refugee Camp as Israel Rejects U.S. Push for Pause in Fighting
description: Israeli warplanes struck a refugee camp in the Gaza Strip, killing at least 40 people and wounding dozens, Palestinian health officials said.

title: Blinken Meets Palestinian President in West Bank as Gaza Assault Escalates
description: Blinken reaffirmed the U.S. commitment to the delivery of life-saving humanitarian assistance and resumption of essential services in Gaza.

title: Protest Marches Across the Globe Call for Immediate Halt to Israeli Bombing of Gaza
description: From Washington to Milan, thousands of pro-Palestinian demonstrators marched Saturday, calling for a halt to Israel’s bombardment of Gaza.
